  "texts": [
    "So, the third fundamental scientific question is as follows: Is the turbulence concept derived from pure mathematical deductions based on a macroscopic continuous image entirely consistent with that in pursuit of physical origin?",
    "(iv) At present, the studies on non-linear systems [48,49] and heat and mass transfer in small systems have made rich progress [50][51][52][53][54][55][56][57][58].",
    "Heat and mass transfer in small systems exhibit some behaviors that seem \"anomalous\" (different from the macroscopic continuous cases) and have attracted significant attention in the fields of statistical physics and nonlinear science [59].",
    "However, it is worth noting that the small systems extensively studied in the literature of statistical physics and nonlinear science are often much smaller than the mesoscale nonequilibrium situations of interest in the mechanical engineering field.",
    "The situation we face is that engineering applications largely rely on macroscopic continuous modeling, but also encounter unsatisfactory or even unsolvable problems."
